cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.SE, cs.AI 

This paper discusses a collaborative defense strategy to tackle the Mirai botnet, which targets out-of-date IoT devices. The paper focuses on cybersecurity (cs.CR) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) as it deals with IoT devices and their vulnerabilities. The paper also discusses the implementation of a prototype system, which falls under systems and control (cs.SY) and software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper mentions the use of a "white" Mirai, which involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques.
